<item>
            <title>[JCR-1770] RFC4918 feature: absolute paths in &quot;Destination&quot; and &quot;If&quot; headers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1770</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>RFC4918 allows absolute paths (instead of absolute URIs) in the &amp;quot;Destination&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;If&amp;quot; headers (&amp;lt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://greenbytes.de/tech/webdav/rfc4918.html#rfc.section.14.8&amp;gt;)&quot;&gt;http://greenbytes.de/tech/webdav/rfc4918.html#rfc.section.14.8&amp;amp;gt;)&lt;/a&gt;. This makes it simpler to deal with situations where reverse proxies are involved (because those usually are not aware of WebDAV request headers and do not rewrite them).</description>
                <environment></environment>
