                    <comment id="12638274" author="reschke" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2008 13:34:15 +0100"  >Support for absolute paths was added as part of fixing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1782&quot; title=&quot;Destination header not containing URI scheme causes NPE&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-1782&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Support for absolute paths in the &amp;quot;If&amp;quot; header is sort of present already, as the servlet currently ignores entries for resources other than the request URI (see associated ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1785&quot; title=&quot;If header checking lacks etag checks&quot;&gt;JCR-1785&lt;/a&gt;).</comment>
                    <comment id="12638279" author="reschke" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2008 13:47:47 +0100"  >Marking as fixes, as the outstanding issue on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1785&quot; title=&quot;If header checking lacks etag checks&quot;&gt;JCR-1785&lt;/a&gt; affects RFC2518 compliance as well.</comment>
